HEADWORD: Child study
<hw>Child study</hw>. <def>A scientific study of children, undertaken
for the purpose of discovering the laws of development of the body and
the mind from birth to manhood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

